p: Expression values for all 1310 proteins in each infection were uploaded into the Ingenuity Pathway Analysis (IPA) tool. For this we expanded consideration of dysregulated proteins to those significantly dysregulated >1.33-fold to increase the number of analyzed molecules to nearly 100. As reflected by the numbers of dysregulated proteins induced by each virus ( Table 1 and Table 2; Figure 1A), PR8-infected A549 cells demonstrated a moderately global positive Z-score, RV733 and pdm09-infected cells showed no significant positive or negative Z-score, and both H5N1- and H7N9-infected cells showed overall negative Z-scores ( Figure 2).
